" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/27/01 12:24:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9236.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Umbral Plains question</span><hr size=1> Also note that many of the mobs are unsnarable (but strangely, some of the same mobs are rootable). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umaldaven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maldaven</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/27/01 12:52:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9236.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Umbral Plains question</span><hr size=1> I made a special hotkey for pulling in Umral<br>
<br>
/g Go go ghetto pathing [ %t ] inc!<br>
<br>
Pulling to the zone in is quite fun, puller ganks 3 as soon as they start coming in the tunnel they run off sometimes bringing more back, sometimes bringing less...  Another fun feature in umbral is the MoB's warping under the world and hitting the puller (who can't see them).<br>
<br>
VI's pathing hasn't gotten better as the technology improves, it's actually getting mucho worse.  Just look at Hate's 2nd floor, puller can have the whole second floor aggro'd on them and not a single one can path to where they are.  They just run around in circles. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/upredatoryinstinct.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Predatory Instinct</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/27/01 2:42:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9236.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Umbral Plains question</span><hr size=1> Oh and another thing about UP.<br>
<br>
Do not ever ever cast on them until it is nuke time, you will never get agro off the caster who cast on the mob until they die...no matter what spell they cast.<br>
<br>
Even if the mob is at 50% life from MT, it will agro, period.<br>
<br>
This is what we did:<br>
<br>
Chanter_01 shouts 'MOB_01 TASHED!'<br>
Chanter_01 zones out then back in.<br>
<br>
Shaman_01 shouts 'MOB_01 SLOWED!'<br>
Shaman zones out then back in.<br>
<br>
Then at about 25% hp left:<br>
Raid Leader_01 shouts 'Nuke Now!' <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udalteneq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DaltenEQ</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/27/01 3:10:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9236.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Umbral Plains question</span><hr size=1> The thing with mobs is not the pathing, but their AI.<br>
<br>
The AI is horrible, when you pull a 2nd floor hate mob to the first floor, you'd expect the pathing to be fine, but its actually the same or worse.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utelon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Telon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/27/01 3:10:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9236.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Umbral Plains question</span><hr size=1> Spent quite a bit of time in UP this week, killing gantru then later dark assassins/masters.  Didn't have any of the aggro problems you mention, warriors could taunt mobs off cleric/chanter, as could I with a snare or 2.  It was definately a challenge, but doable with a good high level group (we were all 60, ranger x 2 warrior cleric enchanter bard).  Was a heck of a lot of fun.<br>
<br>
The dark masters dropped level 58 rng/bst spells and dark master armor which has the same stats as dark assassin armor, bard/rog only.  Don't remember any of the stats offhand, but they were about equivalent to pog/thurg armor I think, maybe with better stats/saves. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unaathankaine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Naathan Kaine</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.tripod.com/~Mystiqal/newanim/cosmic/dancingteke.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/27/01 3:20:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9236.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Umbral Plains question</span><hr size=1> Heh, this zone is the worse one i've seen yet. As soon as you take a couple of steps out of the zone, the Dark Assassin at the entrace to the zone aggros on you, , pulling singles is not possible. Those Dark Assassins have the aggro range of wuoshi and there are alot of them. Cant just pull 1, you pull about 5 from casting/shooting arrow on 1, gain the aggro of about 4 more mobs on the way back to camp, and if yer lucky, the crappy pathing only brings 3 to your group while the rest figure out how to get to you. Also, there are just too many mobs in the zone(mobs packed too close together with too high a aggro range). You cant hack a lugie without hitting 3 or 4 blue mobs. Only good thing is that the majority dont seem to see invis or sneak/hide so you can pretty much roam the zone at will and see those interesting weaps those Dark Assassins sometimes hold and wonder wtf exactly is it since you cant pull them anyhow without having a raid force in place to handle all the adds. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uauserpentsonoblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AuSerpent Sonoblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/27/01 3:27:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9236.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Umbral Plains question</span><hr size=1> I didn't notice any abnormal spell aggro either of the 2 times I've been here.  Tash and slow are high aggro spells and you just have to treat them as such.  We had a enchanter doing tash/slow/cripple and she never got aggro off our Main tank.  Our wizzie that was there one night didn't gain aggro the whole night either.  You just need tanks that can taunt and casters that know a couple things bout aggro control.<br>
<br>
As for pulling, if you are pulling to the zone you have to stop at the end of the hallway in and let them swing at you and walk backwards into the fighting area and they will follow you in just fine.<br>
<br>
As stated several times, Dark Assassin aggro is huge.  I would often aggro one I couldn't even see while pulling.  We would just stick tanks on the DA's first and mez everything else till the DA was dead.  The other stuff is large aggro but predictable.<br>
<br>
Drop rates were very low for us.  Anybody know  any use for the gems besides merchant fodder? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umeelz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Meelz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/27/01 9:36:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9236.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Umbral Plains question</span><hr size=1> Dark Assassins can not be mezed and do not count as undead. We took a group down there and just pulled stuff at the zone... got lots of Tarmok looking guys, dark assassins, and one or two of those yellow aliena d00ds. All can be slowed and rooted. Assassins can not be mezed tho so if you get a assassin add, change target to assassin and mez tarmokwannabe. Do not turn your back on an assassin or else you'll get a nice 500 backstab landed on ya. Never really got more than 3 mobs on a pull... pathing sux at tunnel too... pull a mob and come down tunnel. then before it gets to you, he turns around and starts running away back to the tunnel entrance, then he come for ya... Loot sux too. About 2 hours there and only thing dropped was off ASsassin... a +3% hide dagger with rusty weapon stats. Woot! Went to pet.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/urolemeggido.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Role Meggido</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/27/01 9:42:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9236.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Umbral Plains question</span><hr size=1> f as in f Umbral Plains <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udiscordkitty.showPublicProfile?language=EN>discordkitty</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/28/01 12:40:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9236.topic&index=12>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Umbral Plains question</span><hr size=1> hrm I was there a while this evening, wandered way out from the zone in, group consisted of me (58 cleric), 60 warrior, 60 druid, 60 wizard, 58 SK, 60 paladin (no CC, no slows etc) and we didn't have a problem... pulled in 1's or 2's, never had to run and zone... rarely if ever got heal aggro... far from uber <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udiscordkitty.showPublicProfile?language=EN>discordkitty</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0> at: 12/28/01 12:42:35 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uferessa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Feressa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/28/01 8:37:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9236.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Umbral Plains question</span><hr size=1> The zone is definitely NOT the best place to fight in Umbral. Find a nice spot on the wall somewhere and you can pull with at most 1-2 adds. Pathing is also a lot better away from the zone tunnel. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usanterre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Santerre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/28/01 12:55:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9236.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Umbral Plains question</span><hr size=1> Nice thing about this zone is you get a better drop rate than Thurg quest armor w/ sameish stats, better than planar armor, and trivial CR if you get wiped.   You can pull/kite/peel most of zone similar to castle strategy in Fear - just use SoE as the DAs are SoW speed.  It's fun for a while, but I see it more as a 50-55 raid zone rather than a 60 xp zone.<br>
<br>
Respawn rate is DAMN fast tho - you have to move from zone if you want different mob types (different drops). <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showMessage?topicID=9118.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showMessage?topicID=9267.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9236.topic&index=14><img src=http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.emailToFriend?topicID=9236.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.threadControl?topicID=9236.topic><img src=http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/closeThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=9236.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=9236.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion">Main Lounge<option value="thesaf